<subSubSection id="C3066554FFBDAF24B0CCEB4575345993" pageId="14" pageNumber="545" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA336DFFFBDAF24B0CCEB4575345993" blockId="14.[151,1437,295,1509]" pageId="14" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis id="B968EACDFFBDAF24B0CCEB4576555977" bold="true" box="[199,328,1375,1401]" pageId="14" pageNumber="545">Etymology</emphasis>
. The scientific name derives from the Latin vitta meaning band, referring the presence of a distinct black band on the frons of the head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3066554FFBDAF24B0CCEBBD75B959EB" pageId="14" pageNumber="545" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA336DFFFBDAF24B0CCEBBD75B959EB" blockId="14.[151,1437,295,1509]" pageId="14" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis id="B968EACDFFBDAF24B0CCEBBD762659CF" bold="true" box="[199,315,1447,1473]" pageId="14" pageNumber="545">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is closely similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D5CFFBDAF24B2C9EBB274E059CC" authority="(Zetterstedt)" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[706,1021,1447,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Megaphthalmoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unilineatus">
<emphasis id="B968EACDFFBDAF24B2C9EBB2747B59CF" box="[706,870,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="545">M. unilineatus</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from it by characteristics mentioned in the following key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
